review_blob: A very good trappist type ale. Flowery aroma with slighty sweet palate. Medium body with sweet finish. A good Belgian.

Very nice drinkable Belgian. Nice head forms when poured into tulip galss. Totally different flavor when poured into a pint glass. The tulip pour was heady with a slight hop bite. The pint pour was like drinking a Bud.

Ver surprised by the 8%, it does not taste strong. A fruity banana aroma at first then becomes very sweet. Nice head when poured from bottle that lasts for a few sips. By the end of the glass sweetness was taking over.
Not a bad beer. Beats Bud and Coors with a nice flavor with some bitterness. Great for summer and watching the game with your pals.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Pours a beautiful colour honey becomes very over powering after a few slurps. Good though on a hot day.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Starts with pleasant armoa giving blackberry notes on first taste. Becomes somewhat bitter after third taste, but never overpowering.
Draught: Started nice with a rich thick head. Tasted of roasted malt and some nice hops. After a few more sips it started to leave a sickly sweet aftertaste. Adjuncts??
Draught: Very nice creamy pour. Leavesa nice head tha sticks around for the entire pint. Creamy taste with nice hopping and maltiness.
I guess for low carb it isnt bad but.. Pours a nice yellow with a head that disappears in seconds. Way over-carbonated, which distracted from the taste.
A nice chocolate aroma as you open the bottle. Good malt tast at first which by the end was somewhat to sweet.
Nice malty aroma and taste after pouring. Then a sickly sweet  aftertaste. The head actually last after the first sip. Nice lace.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: A very nice beer. Nice head that stays with good malt and hops coming thru to the finish.
Has a nice floral aroma at first which tricks you into thinking this will be good. HAAA just another macro swill.
Had this on tap. Nice frothy head with good malt nose. Slight sweet aste with choclate hiding somewhere. Paired well with prime-rib.
The safe choice when going out at night. Has good flavor nice hops and good malts.
Awesome head due to the nitro capsule. A nice ale not to heavy or light. Creamy texture with nothing really remarkable about it.
Doesnt stout mean a nice dark dark thick drink? Well this stuff has the color of old coke that sat in the sun.  Vanilla flavor is there but not much else.

Nice amber color as you pour the beer, has a nice aroma of malt. Not much head or lacing happening and seems like natural carb as opposed to being pumped in. Very Very drinkable. Will drive from Mi. to Pa. to get some more.
A bit more flavor than regular Labatt. Must be the extra alcohol. The aroma is hoppy with floral overtones.
Not bad for a light. It will always taste, look and smeel better than a Bud.
A malty aroma as the top pops off, followed by a nice malt mouth feel. Light head and a little bit of hops. This would be a good beer with a BBQ steak.
A well balanced hop flavor with good nose and head. A IPA that can be had all night. Decent head and nice lacing make this a fine IPA.
UPDATED: MAY 4, 2005
Very tasty with a good amber color and nice head. Was served in a warm glass that wiped out the head but did help with flavor as opposed to a chilled mug.
This is what ale should aspire to. All the elements work and work well. Amber color lots of lace and maltineess with light hops. mmmm

OH MY GOD!! a product by Bud that tastes respectable. No rice and a golden color that beer should have. Seems like they are trying to copy either Budvar or a Heinie. Decent head with some lace action and a a what.. hops. Maybe someone told AB that Bud sucks and they are trying to redeem themselves.
This beer does what it set out to do. It's their version of BD. LT. and it succeds at it. Not much taste or aroma but if you want to drink all day this is it.

Drank this beer after it had sat for 10 minutes and had warmed up a bit. Very aggressive hoppiness with a maltiness that was quite pleasing. Do not drink this right off they serve it to cold. LET IT WARM UP!!!
Very nice roasted malt flavor. Good head and creamy finish. Belgian lace was noticable with a nice bitterness.
This beer has a really cool logo. Other than that the beer is garbage. It has no head and very little aroma except for a very faint floral scent.
This is tough, how do you rate nothing?? No taste, palate or anything resembling beer.
Just what you would expect from a macro-brew. Fizzy with little real taste. Have it with a hamburger.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Very tasty, has a nice head a good aftertaste. There is a different taste when drinking from bottle, much better from glass.
Had to drink this while the Blackout was happening. Lets see... no power, beer getting warm, drink quick. Not much taste.. so much the better.
Nice heady flavor full of malt. Nice Belgian lace with a nice bite to finish it off. Had this while having ribs and it complimented the meal quite nicely.
Very hoppy but not overly anoying. Nice head good flavor and a pleasent aftertaste. Goes down easy with a meal.
This is Mich. ultra on steroids. Has .001% more taste than Ultra. Lots of fizz and you know I think my pee is darker.
I wonder what this tastes like on the old sod. Everytime a beer comes over the pond it turns to rot gut or is contract brewed by the Big 3 and ruined.
Spicy with fruit undertones. Hard to find fresh here in Mi. Good hop flavor and nice Belgian lace.
As close to heaven as I'll ever get. Very heady and all around good stuff . Not as good as Guinness from a beer engine but as good as can be expected.
On tap very good, nice aroma etc. In the bottle I cannot find a store with good turnover and the beer is always old and musty.
Very hit or miss. If you find it chilled and had been kept chilled and in the dark you will love it. If it has seen light or warmth forget it.
Oh my god the skunky aftertaste makes it seem like an elephant stepped on your tongue.
One of the advantages of living in Detroit is going over the river to get fresh Sleemans. A very tasty and smooth beer. Nothing to surprise anyone in this beer just plain ole tastes ggod.
Well this proves that Coors can make a beer with good taste, now why don't they do it with their flagship brand?

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Good roasted malt flavor, not to much in the way of bitterness. Good lace showing along with a nice nose.
A very tasty ale. Noticed choclate overtones and quite hoppy. goes perfect for an after dinner ale.
It quenchs my thirst and I get what i pay for. Affordable and no crummy aftertaste... I can't believe I'm writing this.
It was given life when an independent Strohs bought it but by the time it got to Pabst they put the corn stalk through the coffin.
It used to be good when independent not it stinks. It has no head or flavor not to mention any taste.
